Source: Times of India, AFP Report, filed Tue 24 Oct 2000 [edited

Death Tolls of Rift Valley fever Outbreak in Saudi Arabia and Yemen
-------------------------------------------------------------------
RIYADH: A total of 10 new cases of Rift Valley fever (RVF), a virus
affecting Saudi Arabia and Yemen since September, were reported over the
past 24 hours, the Ministry Of Health said here on Sun 22 Oct 2000. "10 new
cases of RVF were recorded ... bringing to 433 the number of people affected
by the sickness, of whom 210 have left hospital after being cured," the
Ministry said in a statement. No new fatalities were reported. This is the
second successive day that the Ministry has not reported any death. The last
death toll released Fri 20 Oct 2000 reported 84 dead.
In Yemen, 71 people have died since the virus appeared in early September.
The World Health Organisation has launched an appeal for 975 000 US dollars
to help
boost international efforts to counter the disease in Yemen.
